{
  "text": "Exosomes were prepared as described previously [CITATION_1] . After thawing on ice, CSF was centrifuged at 15,000 \u00d7 g for 10 min to pellet any shed cells, large membrane fragments, and other debris. The supernatant was then centrifuged at 200,000 \u00d7 g for 60 min. The pellet was resuspended in 1\u00d7PBS and then re-centrifuged at 200,000 \u00d7 g for 60 min before final resuspension in 1\u00d7PBS. The protein content of exosomes was determined using the BCA protein assay kit (Pierce, Rockford, IL, USA). Finally, the exosome fractions were dissolved in SDS sample buffer for immunoblotting.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "1635349"
  },
